From: MediaTek MT7921U Driver Team <mt7921u@mediatek.com>
Date: Thu, 6 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: mt7921: implement remaining source-level features

Implement 5 source-level features for the mt7921u driver:

TASK-017: Multi-Endpoint TX QoS
- Add num_out_eps field to struct mt76_usb to track OUT endpoint count
- Extend mt76u_set_endpoints() to accept 2-6 OUT endpoints (was strict 4)
- Add 6-endpoint mapping in mt76u_ac_to_hwq() with per-AC dedicated
  endpoints (EP0: BK, EP1: BE, EP2: VI, EP3: VO, EP4: MCU, EP5: FWDL)
- Fallback to existing 2-3 endpoint mapping for older configurations
- Add dev_dbg() when 6 endpoints are detected vs fallback
- RUNTIME_VERIFY: verify endpoint count with lsusb -v

TASK-018: Per-Chunk Firmware ACK
- Add fw_ack_enable module parameter (bool, default 0)
- Log dev_info() when ACK mode is enabled during firmware download
- Mirrors vendor driver's DOWNLOAD_CONFIG_ACK_OPTION (BIT(31)) mechanism
- DL_MODE_NEED_RSP is already set by default; the module param serves
  as an explicit opt-in for logging and future per-chunk ACK handling
- RUNTIME_VERIFY: verify firmware download succeeds with ACK enabled

TASK-013: DFS Master Preparation (stub)
- Add UNI_RDD_ON_OFF_CTRL sub-command enum for MCU_UNI_CMD_RDD_CTRL
- Add struct mt7921_dfs_state with radar_detected, cac_band_idx, cac_time_ms
- Add dfs_state to struct mt792x_phy
- Register .start_radar_detection mac80211 op
- Implementation sends UNI_RDD_ON_OFF_CTRL to firmware, records request
- CAC logic is stubbed — actual timing depends on firmware
- RUNTIME_VERIFY: CAC timing depends on firmware

TASK-016: BT Coexistence Detection
- Handle MT_NIC_CAP_COEX in mt7921_mcu_get_nic_capability()
- Store capability in dev->bt_coex_supported (new bool field)
- Log dev_info() when firmware reports coex support
- Create debugfs file bt_coex showing coex state
- RUNTIME_VERIFY: verify coex capability with BT headset active

TASK-012: HW Timestamping
- Store 64-bit TSF from RX descriptor Group 2 in status->mactime
- Advertise NL80211_FEATURE_HW_TIMESTAMP in wiphy features
- .get_tsf op already exists (mt792x_get_tsf)
- RUNTIME_VERIFY: use linuxptp to measure sync accuracy

Signed-off-by: MediaTek MT7921U Driver Team <mt7921u@mediatek.com>
